attributes.about_this_biz_specialties:
At our Indian restaurant, we take pride in offering a unique dining experience that sets us apart from the rest. attributes.about_this_biz_history: Built in 1913 by Campbell River Lumber Co. The building was originally a lumber mill, employing over 400 workers to cut lumber produced for building trenches in Russia during WWI. The building has had many uses, among them; a Presbyterian church, a school, and living quarters for migrant railroad workers. In 1934, after the mill had shut down, it became the home of Arthur Sharpe who acted as caretaker for the building and the surrounding land. Sharpe was a quiet man who kept to himself. During a stormy night in 1943 locals remember hearing screams of pain echo through the hills. He was never seen again. Some believe he was struck by a train, some say he drowned during a late night swim, other believe he went crazy and locked himself in the building rafters. It's now believed that the old caretaker roams the ground today in spirit. There've been many odd occurrences: items being moved, rooms have been swept, noises have been heard in the ceiling & walls. Let us know if you see Arthur.

attributes.about_this_biz_history: The story of Subway started over 50 years ago when Dr. Peter Buck, a nuclear physicist, changed the life of a student with a few simple words, "Let's open a submarine sandwich shop." It was Peter Buck that gave college freshman Fred DeLuca the idea to open a submarine sandwich shop to help pay his tuition. Peter provided an initial investment of $1K, and a business relationship was forged that changed the landscape of the fast food industry. The partners opened their first restaurant in Bridgeport, Connecticut, where they served fresh, affordable, made to order sandwiches. The popularity of the sandwiches and the brand continued to grow but one thing remained, their core values and principles. By 1974, the duo owned and operated 16 submarine sandwich shops in Connecticut. From there, they began franchising, launching the brand into a period of remarkable growth. Today, the SUBWAY® brand is the world's largest submarine sandwich chain with more than 40,000 locations worldwide.
attributes.about_this_biz_specialties: Making change for good. We're taking a fresh look at how we make an impact on the world around us. It's our responsibility, and we aspire to do better every day. We want everyone to have access to better-for-you options and nutritious food. So innovations, quality control, and transparency are on the menu. Subway® restaurants are owned and operated by your neighbors. We support our communities and lend a hand when one is needed.

attributes.about_this_biz_bio:
Dwayne graduated Northern Alberta Institute of Technology with honors as an Architectural Technologist followed by 4 years working for an Architect before establishing his own Design Firm in 1973. His firm became a leading Architectural/Interior Design/Graphics/ Contract Management firm consulting to major corporations, developers and real estate companies. In 1989 he developed the initial concept and land assembly for the creation of Morgan Creek golf course and housing development.

He has been heavily involved in humanitarian aid to Romania since 1992, which included eight personal trips. He spearheaded matching organizations such as Rotary International bringing material and medical goods while the country was in desperate need. Dwayne's latest hobby is the restoration of his 1977 GMC Classic Motor Home and building playgrounds for his grandchildren.

attributes.about_this_biz_bio:
Where It All Began

First, I will share what God has allowed me to know and tell you a little history about me. My childhood was generally perfect and almost like any other girl. Still, when I grew up, my body was changing and reacting very differently from regular to hard food intolerances; I realized that I needed something different. Frankly, seeing people eat “normal” but not me caused me to get depressed many times. As a result, I did plenty of research to find a cure and discovered unique diets which motivated me to make low-carb and gluten-free breads and desserts. Now, I see a lot of difference in my digestion and mood. So now, I am inspired to help people who do not have many options to take care of their health by eating delicious, nourishing desserts. Hence, it gives me great joy to cook those goodies with unique characteristics you can enjoy!
attributes.about_this_biz_history: Yummy Hope Bakery was lovely created to help people who have struggled with diabetes, celiac disease and dairy intolerance to live a normal life with their loved ones, friends, colleagues, or strangers. Nowadays, many men and women just like me and you cannot eat conventional or quotidian healthy food without dealing with substances and ingredients that can affect their body permanently in many ways.
attributes.about_this_biz_specialties: Gluten-Free, Vegan and Diabetes Friendly Desserts and Treats!

attributes.about_this_biz_history: The story of Sal y Limon is the story of four friends--Carolina and Sebastien and Adriana and Pepe--who wanted to share their passion and bring Vancouver Mexican food that was rich with authentic flavour. attributes.about_this_biz_bio:
Dwayne graduated Northern Alberta Institute of Technology with honors as an Architectural Technologist followed by 4 years working for an Architect before establishing his own Design Firm in 1973. His firm became a leading Architectural/Interior Design/Graphics/ Contract Management firm consulting to major corporations, developers and real estate companies. In 1989 he developed the initial concept and land assembly for the creation of Morgan Creek golf course and housing development.

He has been heavily involved in humanitarian aid to Romania since 1992, which included eight personal trips. He spearheaded matching organizations such as Rotary International bringing material and medical goods while the country was in desperate need. Dwayne's latest hobby is the restoration of his 1977 GMC Classic Motor Home and building playgrounds for his grandchildren.

Now with granddaughter Jessi and her husband, Todd(both certified Red Seal Chefs), new ideas happen all the time at the Turkey House. After all, any time is turkey time ™.
